caption: AA Cajun Seafood restaurant. 214 E Burnside avenue in the Bronx. I ordered from this place in the past and the food was ok. I placed a order today. Shrimp, King Crab legs, Dungeness crab. The Seafood was old, sour and spoiled. It had a horrible rotten smell. The boiled egg, potatoes and corn had a slim coating and horrible smell. I called the company and the owner yelled at me and hung up the phone. I spent 106.00. A waste of my money

I used to order from here often but recently stopped. I think they cut too many corners in order to provide fast service and it’s not worth it in the end.  Pros: -They deliver very fast, I often have my food in 20 mins. -They’re open most holidays. -Their vegetables are usually tasty.  Cons: -The quality of their food does not justify the price increases they’ve made over the last year, in my opinion. -Fast delivery is great but they do not take time to properly clean their shrimp of feces before cooking it alongside other food. -Inspect your chicken next time you buy General Tso’s because it’s tends to be mostly breading and sauce with a little bit of meat in the center. It’s made to look like it’s a lot of meat but there’s not. A mouth full of sauced breading is disgusting.
